contents.description:
JSON containing nested structure to zip


Example
```
{
  "outerzip": {
    "type": "zip",
    "name": "outerzip.zip",
    "content": [
    {
      "type": "file",
      "name": "outerzipfile1.json",
      "content": {
        "file": "json file1 content"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "zip",
      "name": "innerzip.zip",
      "content": [
      {
        "type": "fileRef",
        "name": "innerzipfile1.jpeg",
        "fileIndex": 0
      },
      {
        "type": "fileRef",
        "name": "outerzipfile2.jpeg",
        "fileIndex": 1
      },
      ]
    }
    ]
  }
}

get.description:
Lists Submissions of a particular module (or multiple modules), based on the requesting user's role and group membership, for population of a Dashboard. Supported features:

- Specify specific submission data/metadata fields to include in the query result

- Specify filter conditions based on specific submission data/metadata values

- Specify sort order based on data fields

Submission data filter conditions, sort, skip, and limit must be specified according to the [api-query-params](https://github.com/loris/api-query-params) library.

Example: `/fbu/uapi/system/getSubmissions?moduleId=<module1>&moduleId=<module2>&fields=name,age&filter={"data.age":{"$in":["33"]}}`

Filtering by top level submission fields is permitted for admins and only available for _workflow and status. When more than one filter condition is added for the following fields they will be used to match a single element in the array
- _workflow.state.currentState
- _workflow.state.stateHistory
- status.current
- status.all

Example: `/fbu/uapi/system/getSubmissions?workflowId=<id1>&status.all.key=opened&status.all.user=user1` will match a submission with the following status.all data because the first element meets both filter conditions


    {
      "status": {
        "all": [
          {
            "key": "opened",
            "user": "user1"
          },
          {
            "key": "reviewed",
            "user": "user1"
          }
        ]
      }
    }


`/fbu/uapi/system/getSubmissions?workflowId=<id1>&status.all.key=opened&status.all.user=user1` will not match a submission with the following status.all data because neither element meets both filter conditions


    {
      "status": {
        "all": [
          {
            "key": "opened",
            "user": "user2"
          },
          {
            "key": "reviewed",
            "user": "user1"
          }
        ]
      }
    }

### Authorization Required:
  - See Submission Access <a href="#submission-access" target="_self">Submission Access</a>
